# tkv2 - select: dropdown primitive (std-ui-select)

Slice `std-ui-select` (`specs/std-ui-select.md`): `select` builds a `<select>`
`TkNode` over `(value, label)` pairs, two-way bound to a `Signal[String]`. DOM
serialization (option/selected markup, the change→signal wiring) is covered
by `examples/frontend/select-demo/select-demo.ssc`'s emitted bundle; this
conformance file keeps the public API and the `lower()` path live on both
lanes, and exercises the initial-selection read (`selected()`) that decides
which `<option>` starts marked `selected`.

[signal](std/ui/primitives.ssc)
[select](std/ui/input.ssc)
[lower](std/ui/lower.ssc)
[defaultTheme](std/ui/theme.ssc)

```scalascript
val opts = [("a", "Alpha"), ("b", "Beta"), ("c", "Gamma")]
val picked = signal("tkv2SelectPicked", "b")

println(picked())
picked.set("c")
println(picked())

// Safe named-arg calling convention: name every trailing param from the
// first one overridden onward (see specs/std-ui-select.md "Known
// limitation" — a bin/ssc-run-only standard-tier bug, not this lane).
val node = select(opts, picked, label = "Pick one", placeholder = "Choose...", disabled = false)
val view = lower(node, defaultTheme)
println("select-built")

// placeholder-only path: empty initial selection, disabled render.
val empty = signal("tkv2SelectEmpty", "")
val node2 = select(opts, empty, label = "", placeholder = "Nothing yet", disabled = true)
val view2 = lower(node2, defaultTheme)
println("select-disabled-built")
```
